<span class="admin"> <a name="home_status"></a>
<h3>Application Status</h3>
This page shows system status information. It shows you the current state of
your Cyclos system as well as relevant open alerts, logged in users, and
application errors.<br>
The underlined numbers and items in the page can be clicked for further details.
Click the &quot;Refresh&quot; link at the bottom of the page to update the
information displayed.
<br><br>Application Status displays the following:
<ul>
	<li><b>Cyclos version:</b> Cyclos Version of installation. Cyclos uses the
	release timestamp as version number.
	<li><b>Application uptime:</b> The time that Cyclos is running in hours
	and minutes.
	<li><b>Unread messages:</b> The number of unread <a
		href="${pagePrefix}messages"><u>messages</u></a> from members to the
	administration.
	<li><b>Open system invoices:</b> The number of open <a
		href="${pagePrefix}invoices"><u>invoices</u></a> from system
	accounts to members.
	<li><b>Number of connected admins:</b> Number of connected admins at this moment.
	Select the number to open a list with the admins.
	<li><b>Number of connected members:</b> Number of connected members at
	this moment. Select the number to open a list with the members.
	<li><b>Number of connected brokers: </b> Number of connected brokers at
	this moment. Select the number to open a list with the brokers.
	<li><b>Number of system alerts:</b> Total number of open <a
		href="${pagePrefix}alerts_logs#system_alerts"><u>system alerts</u></a>. Select
	the number to open a list with the alerts.
	<li><b>Number of member alerts:</b> Total number of open <a
		href="${pagePrefix}alerts_logs#member_alerts"><u>member alerts</u></a>. Select
	the number to open a list with the alerts.
	<li><b>Application errors:</b> Total number of open <a
		href="${pagePrefix}alerts_logs#error_log"><u>application errors</u></a>.
	Select the number to open a list with the errors.
</ul>
