<span class="member"> <a name="home_news"></a>
<h3>News (message board)</h3>
The message board will show relevant news items. The contents of this box is
completely dependent on your organization, and what your administrators decided
to put into it.<br>
Generally, it shows messages to all members.
These messages are sent by the administrator and can
concern any interesting news for the users or important information
about the organization or the system, like changes, new users, features
etc.
<hr class="help">
</span>

<span class="admin">
<a name="jump_to_profile"></a>
<h3>Jump to Member profile</h3>
This window is a quick way to access the profile of a member. Just enter
the member's name (or his login name) in one of the edit fields. The
fields are auto-completed: typing a few letters will show you all available
options. <br>
As soon as it is clear which member you want to see, the program will jump
to the <a href="${pagePrefix}profiles"><u>profile</u></a> of this member.
<hr class="help">
</span>

<a name="home_invite"></a>
<h3>Invite</h3>
If you enter an e-mail address of a friend or an acquaintance, and click
&quot;Send&quot;, an e-mail will be sent to this person, inviting them to try
out the software and the system. Your name will be mentioned in this email as
the sender.
<br>If you want to see the email text before sending it, you could just check
it out and try it with your own e-mail address; you should receive the email
shortly after having clicked &quot;Submit&quot;.
